<section xml:id="structs_vocabulary"
         xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Vocabulary</title>
  <p>
    <dl>
    <li>
      <title>structure:</title>
      <p>A collection of data grouped together and treated as a single object.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <title>enumeration:</title>
      <p>To list things one by one. In programming it means assigning numbers to a list of symbols and treating those symbols as a new data type.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <title>instance:</title>
      <p>An example from a category. My cat is an instance of the category <q>feline things.</q>
        Every struct variable is an instance of its type.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <title>member (or instance) variable:</title>
      <p>One of the named pieces of data that make up a structure.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <title>pure function:</title>
      <p>A function whose result depends only on its parameters, and that has
        so effects other than returning a value.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <title>modifier:</title>
      <p>A function that changes one or more of the objects it receives as parameters, and usually
        returns <c>void</c>.</p>
    </li>
    </dl>
  </p>
</section>